HEADWORD: Prosencephalon
<hw>Pros`en*ceph"a*lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ toward, near to + E. <ets>encephalon</ets>.]</ety>
<altsp>[Sometimes abbreviated to <abbr>proen.</abbr>]</altsp>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The anterior segment of the brain,
including the cerebrum and olfactory lobes; the forebrain.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The cerebrum.</def> <rj><au>Huxley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

